-- Globalive’s Wind Mobile May Get Cash From Orascom, Globe Says
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2010-10-01T11:35:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/globalive-s-wind-mobile-may-get-cash-injection-from-orascom-globe-reports.html
Canadian wireless carrier Globalive
Communications Corp. may get a cash injection from Orascom
Telecom Holding SAE, the Globe and Mail reported today.  Globalive’s Wind Mobile unit is in the final stages of
securing several hundred million dollars of new financing from
Orascom, its Cairo-based financial backer, according to the
Toronto-based newspaper, citing an interview with Wind Chairman
 Anthony Lacavera .  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Doug Alexander  in Toronto at 
 dalexander3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
